<body>
<big style="font-family: lucida console;"><big>Trip to Wakayama &amp;
Shirahama(Dec.29.2002)<br>
<br>
</big></big><img src="021231/02123102.jpg"
 alt="" title="" style="width: 400px; height: 300px;" align="left"><small><span
 style="font-family: lucida console;">We stayed at an inn named </span><a
 href="http://www.naxnet.or.jp/%7Ehayama"
 style="font-family: lucida console;">UMITSUBAKI HAYAMA </a><span
 style="font-family: lucida console;">(KISHYU OKUSHIRAHAMA TSUBAKI hot
spring). There are only six rooms and you can&nbsp; see the ocean in
front of the room directly if you stay. Since the inn was designed by a
famous architecture designer whose name I forget, it has an odd but cool
style. However, you will relax&nbsp; because&nbsp; it is made of many
woods.</span></small><br>
<br>
<a href="http://www.naxnet.or.jp/%7Ehayama">海椿葉山</a>(紀州奥白浜椿温泉）に宿泊してきました。
６部屋しかない旅館で、各部屋の窓から海を直接眺めることができるようになっています。とある建築家の設計で、なかなか奇抜な建物となっています。でも、
木材をふんだんに使っているので、温かみはあるかな。<br>
<img src="021231/02123113.jpg" alt=""
 title="" style="width: 400px; height: 300px;" align="left"><img
 src="021231/02123112.jpg" alt="" title=""
 style="width: 400px; height: 300px;" align="left"><br>
<br>
<small><span style="font-family: lucida console;">The following two
pictures show the ceilings&nbsp; of the room I stayed. The ceilings, as
you know, are&nbsp; corrugated&nbsp; boards used for walls or
fences&nbsp; at a factory. The designer arranged several </span><a
 style="font-family: lucida console;">fluorescent lights between the
boards well. On second thought,&nbsp; was&nbsp; the&nbsp; inn built at
a low cost?(-.-;</a></small><br>
<br>
この写真と下の写真は、宿泊した部屋の天井です。これは言わずとしれた、工場の壁や塀に使用される波板です。そして、波板同士の間に蛍光灯をうまい具合に
配置してあります。冷静に考えるとこれってローコスト住宅?(-.-;<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<img src="021231/02123101.jpg" alt=""
 title="" style="width: 400px; height: 300px;" align="left"><br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<small><span style="font-family: lucida console;">The photograph shows
the view from my room. Since&nbsp; I arrived&nbsp; after sunset, the
view was dull.</span><br style="font-family: lucida console;">
</small><br>
窓の外の景色です。着いたのが日が落ちてからだったので、もうすでに暗いです。ちょっとどんよりした感じで海が写っています。<br>
<img src="021231/02123111.jpg" alt=""
 title="" style="width: 400px; height: 300px;" align="left"><br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<small><span style="font-family: lucida console;">The photograph was
took from my room next day, which was marvelous. Since the room's
window faces west, I would see the scene of sunset if I could arrived
more early.</span><br style="font-family: lucida console;">
</small><br>
次の日の朝の窓景色はすばらしかったです。方向は、西向きなので本当は海に沈む夕日が見れたんでしょうね。。。。<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<img src="021231/02123104.jpg" alt=""
 title="" style="width: 300px; height: 400px;" align="left"><br>
<small><span style="font-family: lucida console;">The photograph shows
a symbol of the South. That is a Japanese sago palm. You will wonder
where I am. Here is......</span></small><span
 style="font-style: italic;"><br>
<br>
</span>南国の象徴ソテツ？です。私、ソテツを見るとなんだか嬉しくなります。で、ここはどこかって？ここは。。。<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<img src="021231/02123%82P03.jpg" alt=""
 title="" style="width: 400px; height: 300px;" align="left"><small><span
 style="font-family: lucida console;">Here is a southern tip of the
main island of Japan. I felt to be surrounded by the sea at 270 degrees.
Also, I could see the horizon.</span><br
 style="font-family: lucida console;">
</small><br>
ここはというと、本州最南端である潮岬です。２７０度ぐるっと海に囲まれている感じです。水平線もよく見えます。<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<big><big><big><br style="font-weight: bold;">
</big></big></big>
<div style="text-align: center;"><big><big><big><span
 style="font-weight: bold;">Underwater Show by AMA(Woman Divers)</span></big></big></big><br>
</div>
<big><big><big></big></big></big>
<div style="text-align: center;"><big><big><big>海女さん水中ショウ（笑）</big></big></big><br>
</div>
<br>
<img src="021231/02123108.jpg" alt=""
 title="" style="width: 400px; height: 300px;" align="left"><img
 src="021231/02123109.jpg" alt="" title=""
 style="width: 400px; height: 300px;" align="left"><small><span
 style="font-family: lucida console;">SHIRAHAMA
hot spring was a deserted place when we visited. It's no wonder because
it was winter. When I went to the SHIRAHAMA coast, there was a
signboard "Underwater Show by woman divers."</span><br
 style="font-family: lucida console;">
</small><br>
白浜温泉は、なかなか良い感じで寂れていました。冬だから当たり前か。浜辺に行くと、怪しい看板がありました。海女さん水中ショウ（笑）<br>
<br>
<br>
<small><span style="font-family: lucida console;">Since there was
nothing interesting, I determined to ride a ship to
watch the show. The floor of the ship has windows and I could see&nbsp;
swimming fishes and sea urchins.</span><br
 style="font-family: lucida console;">
</small><br>
他に面白そうな物もないので乗ってみることにしました。船に乗ってみると船底がガラス張りとなっていて、魚が泳いでいるのが良く見えます。ウニもいた
な<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<img src="021231/02123107.jpg" alt=""
 title="" style="width: 400px; height: 300px;" align="left"><img alt=""
 src="021231/02123105.jpg" title=""
 style="width: 400px; height: 300px;" align="left"><br>
<img src="021231/02123106.jpg" alt=""
 title="" style="width: 400px; height: 300px;" align="left"><small><span
 style="font-family: lucida console;">This picture is the underwater
show by AMAs. They dived under our ship in spite of&nbsp; the cold
temperature. Moreover, they did not catch any fishes but did a forward
roll and so on. At the finish of the show.....&nbsp; You should make
sure what&nbsp; happen there.</span><br
 style="font-family: lucida console;">
<span style="font-family: lucida console;">I regret that I could not
capture the scene.</span><br style="font-family: lucida console;">
</small><br>
そして、これが、問題の海女さんショウです。くそ寒いのにもぐってます（笑）しかも、魚を取るわけでもなく、ただでんぐり返ししたりしてます。そして、最
後のクライマックスは。。。。ご自分でお確かめください。（笑）<br>
写真に収めることができなかったです。<br>
ちょっと残念。<br>
